ay be primarily attributed to (i) human interventions, after Second World War,\non these rivers because of their use for water consumption and (ii) climate\nchange in recent time.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 Jan 2013 07:28:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 25 Sep 2013 11:07:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-12"}
